i stepped on my guinea pig not on purpose but what should i do she seems all right how unfortunate though it happens to the best of us depending on how you stepped on her it may be in her best interest to take her to a veterinarian it's in a guinea pig's nature to hide any signs of illness or distress so thoroughly examine your pig to see if she exhibits any signs of discomfort if you feel she isn't injured let her be but keep an eye on her to make sure she is still eating drinking and expelling waste as per usual any changes whatsoever can be the first sign of something being wrong Guinea pig Domestic rabbit Fecal incontinence Animal testing Dairy Fancy rat Cat Hamster Pig Hypoglycemia Taboo food and drink Characters of Naruto Foodborne illness Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Social rule Elephant Stuttering Invader Zim Anorexia nervosa Whaling Urinary incontinence Prince Edmund (Blackadder) Ron Weasley Self-harm Cancer Chocolate Bloat Ranma __ characters 613 mitzvot A Series of Unfortunate Events Pitaten Human sexual behavior Rat Park Sant Thakar Singh Japanese tea ceremony YuYu Hakusho Eutheism, dystheism, and maltheism The Legend of Zelda series enemies Snuff film Mushroom hunting Grief Tort Abortion debate Spirited Away Theory of conduct Yoga Sutras of Patanjali Livestock Public domain One Tree Hill (TV series) Roman eating and drinking The Smoking Room Economy of Papua New Guinea Meat Vomiting Anxiety Tetrodotoxin Zoophilia Gender identity disorder Garfield Zoonosis Lisa the Vegetarian Milton H. Erickson Sewage treatment Child abuse Yami no Matsuei Poker jargon Debugging Vitamin C Autopsy Fast bowling Chicken Shaggy dog story Procrastination Asperger syndrome Cirrhosis Scientific method Money Coconut crab Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Feces Antarctic Treaty System Horse colic Wood carving The Critic Disease Sara Sidle Happy Tree Friends American Civil Rights Movement (1955-1968) Philosophical skepticism Roswell UFO incident Radiohead Who Framed Roger Rab